Over the past 3 week of reporting, it appears that there have been 5316 additional cases. Although the numbers had decreased, the new period increased averaging about 253 cases PER DAY. The low case fatality rate might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. Although the daily rate had dropped significantly, this many new diarrhea cases per day remains substantial. There was a slowing of cases during the 3-month period of January-March 2017 as well.

A map of Yemen: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5770331,126. - Mod.LL]
